DESIGN
## Plan

**SCOPE DECISION (recommend A-now, defer Hugo):** The bead says "likely using Hugo."
Recommend NOT adopting Hugo for v1. The hand-written narrative docs (docs/{init,
capture,run,sync,replay,bench,gc,reindex}.md + docs/README.md + top-level README)
already satisfy "public docs for implemented behavior." The tight, dependency-free,
high-value deliverable is auto-generating a CLI flag/synopsis REFERENCE from the
cobra tree and committing it under docs/cli/, guarded against drift. Hugo is a
separable, heavier static-site commitment; the markdown produced here is already
the content source if a site is wanted later. Doing Hugo now is the main risk
(new toolchain, theme, CI/deploy) for little gain over clean committed markdown.
DEFER Hugo to its own bead with that reasoning recorded.

**Approach:** Add a small standalone generator at cmd/gen-docs/main.go that builds
the real root command via the already-exported cli.NewRootCommand(io.Discard,
io.Discard) and calls cobra/doc.GenMarkdownTreeCustom into docs/cli/. cobra v1.10.2
already ships github.com/spf13/cobra/doc (GenMarkdownTree/GenMarkdownTreeCustom) -
NO new dependency. A standalone cmd (not a hidden subcommand) keeps the production
binary clean and is trivially invokable from make/go:generate/CI.

**DETERMINISM (critical):** cobra/doc appends "###### Auto generated by spf13/cobra
on <date>" unless cmd.DisableAutoGenTag is true (verified md_docs.go:112-113). The
generator MUST walk the whole command tree and set DisableAutoGenTag=true on the
root AND every subcommand before generating, so committed files are timestamp-free
and diff-stable. Use GenMarkdownTreeCustom with a no-op/relative linkHandler and a
filePrepender that emits only a stable "do-not-edit; run make docs" banner (no date).

**Files:**
- cmd/gen-docs/main.go - NEW. Builds root cmd, disables autogen tag recursively,
  writes docs/cli/*.md via GenMarkdownTreeCustom; takes -out flag (default docs/cli).
- cmd/gen-docs/main_test.go - NEW. Generates into t.TempDir(); asserts one file per
  command (etude.md + etude_bench.md ... etude_sync.md), expected headings/flags
  present, and NO "Auto generated"/date string (determinism guard).
- docs/cli/*.md - NEW generated reference (9 files: root + 8 commands). Committed.
- docs/README.md - add a "CLI reference" link to docs/cli/ (generated, do-not-edit
  note); keep all existing hand-written links untouched (non-clobber: generated
  reference lives only under docs/cli/, never overwrites docs/*.md).
- Makefile - add `docs` target (go run ./cmd/gen-docs) and `docs-check` target
  (regenerate to a temp dir, diff vs committed docs/cli, fail if stale). Optionally
  wire docs-check into the lint/CI path.
- internal/cli/root.go - likely UNCHANGED; NewRootCommand is already exported.
  (If a //go:generate directive is wanted, add one line above it.)

**Tests:**
- Generator writes a deterministic file per command into temp dir.
- Generated output contains command synopsis + flag tables, omits the date footer
  (regenerating twice yields byte-identical output).
- docs-check / drift guard: a test (or the make target) that regen-to-temp + diff
  fails when committed docs/cli is stale - the real engineering value, since
  generated docs that silently rot are worse than none.

**Docs:** This bead IS the docs work. Update docs/README.md to index docs/cli/.
Do not touch the hand-written narrative docs except to link the reference.

**Risks:**
- Hugo scope creep - mitigated by explicit deferral above (MAIN risk).
- Non-deterministic output churning git - mitigated by recursive DisableAutoGenTag +
  date-free filePrepender + a determinism test.
- Doc drift - mitigated by `make docs-check` drift guard (recommend wiring into CI).

